                                                                                                                       7                                      Leander amp; Co. game for CWG
                      
	New Delhi: Indias top tennis players, who had threatened to boycott the Commonwealth Games because of non-payment of dues, Saturday pledged to represent the country in the mega event after being given a categorical assurance that the vexed issues would be resolved soon.         
	 On a day of swift developments, the revolting quartet of Leander Paes, Mahesh Bhupathi, Somdev Dev Varman and Rohan Bopanna made themselves available to play for the country while the Sports Ministry and the AITA also promised to resolve the dispute as early as possible.           (PTI)                                                                                                                 
